com.thinkaurelius.titan.diskstorage.util

Class MetricInstrumentedIterator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.thinkaurelius.titan.diskstorage.util.MetricInstrumentedIterator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    KeyIterator, RecordIterator<StaticBuffer>, Closeable, AutoCloseable, Iterator<StaticBuffer>

    public class MetricInstrumentedIterator
extends Object
implements KeyIterator
    This class is used by MetricInstrumentedStore to measure wallclock time, method invocation counts, and exceptions thrown by the methods on RecordIterator instances returned from MetricInstrumentedStore.getSlice(com.thinkaurelius.titan.diskstorage.keycolumnvalue.KeySliceQuery, com.thinkaurelius.titan.diskstorage.keycolumnvalue.StoreTransaction).
    Author:
    Dan LaRocque

      • of

        public static MetricInstrumentedIterator of(KeyIterator keyIterator,
                            String prefix)
        If the iterator argument is non-null, then return a new MetricInstrumentedIterator wrapping it. Metrics for method calls on the wrapped instance will be prefixed with the string prefix which must be non-null. If the iterator argument is null, then return null.
        Parameters:
        keyIterator - the iterator to wrap with Metrics measurements
        prefix - the Metrics name prefix string
        Returns:
        a wrapper around keyIterator or null if keyIterator is null

      • getEntries

        public RecordIterator<Entry> getEntries()
        Description copied from interface: KeyIterator
        Returns an iterator over all entries associated with the current key that match the column range specified in the query.

        Closing the returned sub-iterator has no effect on this iterator. Calling Iterator.next() might close previously returned RecordIterators depending on the implementation, hence it is important to iterate over (and close) the RecordIterator before calling Iterator.next() or Iterator.hasNext().
